criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Sedentary

          -  >60 year-old in the elderly group or >50 year-old for the PLWH group;

          -  with sarcopenia, as defined by both relative loss of muscle mass by bioimpedentiometry
             (BIA) and low muscle strength by handgrip

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Any disease requiring hospitalization in the 6 weeks before enrollment;

          -  Medical conditions contraindicating the proposed exercise as established by a sport
             medicine specialist;

          -  Current substance or alcohol abuse or use of drugs that may influence balance and
             coordination;

          -  Not being able to walk without assistance and to perform the prescribed exercises as
             by protocol.
